Key Roles & Responsibilities
The key responsibilities for the Financial Market (Commodities/Equities/ FX/Risk) includes:
Write high quality technical specifications from business/functional specifications Contribute to design and implementation of application systems Hands-on programming work for development projects Meet committed project schedules and effort estimates Contribute to implementation and enforcement of development best practices related to standards and control of software code, testing and release management Participate in the recruiting and selection of top quality developers to further grow the team
Qualifications & Skills
Required experience, qualifications and skills:
BSc/MSc degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering from a top tier university Proven hands-on experience in professional application software development Strong oral and written communication skills in English and Mandarin Strong interpersonal skills Demonstrated ability to develop under a SDLC for both traditional waterfall and agile development methodologies High proficiency in hands-on development in the following languages/technology: Object Oriented design and programming Core Java programming, a must have skill C#/.Net programming using WPF, a must have skill RDBMS design and SQL programming, preferably Oracle platform Message based transaction processing architecture Windows, Linux and Unix operating systems
Preferred, but not strictly required experience, qualifications and skills:
Financial industry technology experience Knowledge of Capital Markets businesses and products, including Commodities, Equities, FX, Risk etc
Key Words: Java, J2EE, Spring, Hibernate, Collections, C#, WPF, Commodities, Equities, FX, Risk, Software Development, Tech Lead
McGregor Boyall is an equal opportunity employer and do not discriminate based on race, religion, gender, age, sexuality, gender identification, or physical ability.
